Synchronized swimming exhibition 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 18 (KCNA) -- An exhibition performance of synchronized swimming was given at the swimming pool of the Changgwang Health Complex yesterday to celebrate February 16, the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 Among the audience were senior party and state officials, working people in Pyongyang, congratulatory groups and delegations of overseas compatriots and overseas Koreans.
 Present on invitation were the visiting foreign guests.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The swimming pool was garbed in a splendid festive attire. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than a hundred of performers presented beautiful rhythmic movements with plastic flowers of Kimjongilia, the immortal flower, in their hands to the tune of "Cantata to Comrade  Kim Jong Il." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They made a floral basket of Kimjongilias on the water, representing the warmest congratulation and the best wishes of officers and men of the Korean People's Army and the people from all walks of life to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through powerful sports techniques and artistic depiction rich in national flavor they showed well the great national pride and happiness of the Korean people holding Kim Jong Il in high esteem as their great leader, and their indomitable spirit and optimism in accelerating a dynamic march to build a powerful nation in such numbers as "Our General is Best," "Thunder on Jong Il Peak," "General and Children," "February Means Spring," "Let's Make Faster Leaping Progress and Attain Higher Goals" and "Arirang for Prosperity."

Joint art performance of Korean artistes at home and in U.S. 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 18 (KCNA) -- A joint performance of an art troupe of Koreans in the U.S. and the national symphony orchestra was given at the Yun I Sang Concert Hall yesterday.
 The performance was seen by Han Song Ryong, Choe Yong Rim, chairman of the c.c., the Korean Social Democratic Party Kim Yong Dae and other officials concerned.
 Among the spectators were a congratulatory group of the federation of Koreans in the U.S. headed by its vice-chairperson Ryu Thae Yong, a congratulatory group of the association of Koreans in Australia headed by its chairman Rim Yong Mo and overseas Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The artistes put on stage colorful numbers, including an orchestra "dear leader Kim Jong Il's good health is our happiness" and a female soprano "cantata to comrade  Kim Jong Il." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They impressively depicted the immortal exploits performed by Kim Jong Il, who is praised by all people as the sun of the 21st century, for human cause of independence, and the revolutionary spirit and militant stamina of the Korean people and overseas Koreans who are braving any difficulties and ordeals under his leadership.

War hysteria of U.S. and Japan criticized 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 18 (KCNA) -- The U.S. and Japanese military officials recently had a confab on intensifying cooperation between the U.S. troops and the "self-defence forces" in Washington under the pretext of the DPRK "development of the mass-destruction weapons." in this regard, Rodong Sinmun today runs a commentary, which says it is a dangerous move to unleash a new Korean war.
 Recalling that a few days ago bush announced that not only the "international terrorist organizations" but "those countries developing mass-destruction weapons" would be the target of the U.S. "anti-terrorism war," the news analyst goes on:
 The DPRK development of missiles is to cope with the U.S. pronounced maneuvers to ignite a new war of aggression on Korea and defend the sovereignty of the country. the DPRK can not be the target of the U.S. "anti-terrorism war" for the strengthening of its defence power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While shelving its crimes, the U.S. is keen to militarily stifle the DPRK, groundlessly pulling it up over the non-existent "development of mass-destruction weapons" and listing it as a member of the "axis of evil." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will never pardon the aggressors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bellicose forces should know that it would be a big mistake if they regard the option to strike as their patent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japanese reactionaries should also bear in mind that they would not escape their doom if they join in the Korean war in league with the U.S. imperialists in a bid to achieve their ambition for overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and Japanese reactionaries are well advised to cool down their war fever, mindful that the policy of aggression on Korea is a serious mistake.

Title of Russian honorary academician awarded to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Moscaw, February 15 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il was awarded the title of honorary academician of the academy of social and human studies of the Russian Federation.
 Diploma and badge of honorary academician were conveyed to the DPRK ambassador to Russia by Kaputo, academician of the academy and vice-director of the institute of socio-political issues under the Russian Academy of Sciences, on Feb. 14. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the occasion Kaputo said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il is an outstanding politician who wrote a lot of works and made distinguished contributions to the development of the world social sciences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the greatest honor for us to award the title of honorary academician to him on the occasion of his birthday.

Natural wonder on February holiday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 18 (KCNA) -- A natural wonder and magnificent sunrise were observed in the area of Mt. Paektu on February 16, an auspicious holiday.
 Gusts of wind of 57 m/s blew in fog and snow from Feb. 6, but the fog lifted from Feb. 13.
 The wind began to drop at about 7:20 a.m. on Feb. 16 when the sunrise began.
 At the time, temperature on Mt. Paektu was 14.5 degrees centigrade below zero, highest in February compared with an average year, and the speed of wind was no more than 1 m/s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sky was mysteriously clear and it was very mild. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials of the meteorological observatory on Mt. Paektu and the combined group for surveying Lake Chon on Mt. Paektu commanded a view of the sunrise on Mt. Paektu, the sunrise of Korea in excitement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the area of the secret camp of Mt. Paektu, had been snowy for 60 days since the first snow was recorded on October 10 last year, and the snow around the native home in the secret camp of Mt. Paektu is 60 cm thick as of Feb 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As for the natural wonder and data observed, observers of nature and experts said that the weather of Feb. 16 reminds them of the weather of the historic day when the bright star of Paektu rose.

Foreign guests visit various places in Pyongyang 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 18 (KCNA) -- Delegates of international organizations, delegates and delegations from different regions and countries who had participated in the "Meeting to Congratulate the Sun of the 21st Century" yesterday visited the Tower of the Juche Idea.
 Being briefed on the tower which was built as a grand monumental edifice in the era of the workers' party in order to hand down through generations the revolutionary exploits of President Kim Il Sung who founded the immortal Juche idea and made immortal contributions to the cause of the Korean revolution and the cause of global independence, the guests looked round the tower and group sculptures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they mounted the observation platform of the tower to enjoy a bird's-eye view of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also visited the monument to the three charters for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, He Hong Zhang, chief of the Hotung Society of Trust Funds, Hong Kong, and his party visited the 6th Kimjongilia show. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And they looked round the construction site of the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia exhibition in Pyongyang and visited the Changgwang kindergarten and the youth and juvenile art exhibition to celebrate February 16, the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il, part of the Pyongyang Fine Art Festival.
